stickerText:
1 full week of microdosing peanuts at home alone to desensitize my allergy (under doctor supervision).

Doing this alone has been really hard. REALLY hard. I’ve never had to have this level of fortitude. Leaning on myself. Leaning on my faith. Choosing to face my greatest fear every single day feels like going into a silent battle. I’m so proud of myself for giving this program a shot. 

One more week at this level at home & then we’ll head back to see my doctor for the updose. Onward 🤍

stickerText:
Certain things can make a reaction more likely during OIT — illness, alcohol, exercise to name a few.

Menstruation is one of those things. My doctor went over that with me on FAQ day, but to face it on day 3 before I was even used to the routine/normal risks felt like too much too soon. 

I was so anxious but all was fine & I celebrated with my fav kombucha in a my new champagne flutes 💖

stickerText:
Starting peanut treatment for my severe allergy is going to be the most brave thing I’ve ever done. 

It’s facing down my biggest fear, what has haunted me every day of my life.

It’s not for everyone, but here’s why I want to give it a try. I’m doing it for future me. To do something about the anxiety & fear that is eating at my mental health. To be the best (possible) mom/partner/elderly person in the future.

Maybe it won’t be for me, but just trying it so I never have to wonder “what if” is my definition of success 💖

contents.desc: Pt 8 — Wish me luck 🥹 I’m so scared. I’m so grateful I’ve found a doctor I trust so much and that he’s offered me the opportunity for me to at least try it. If you’re the praying kind, send up an extra one for me tomorrow am. I need it! #peanutallergy #treenutallergy
